The paper deals with matrix recovery from random linear measurements, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an algorithm based on approximate message passing, which is a popular technique in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves numerical optimization and linear algebra, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with matrix estimation, which is a topic in computer vision and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
